  "prompt": "What would be the quadratic equation for the roots 2+\u221a2 and 2-\u221a2?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) If the roots are 2+\u221a2 and 2-\u221a2, the quadratic equation will be in the form:\n   (x - (2+\u221a2))(x - (2-\u221a2)) = 0\n\n2) Expanding this:\n   (x - 2 - \u221a2)(x - 2 + \u221a2) = 0\n\n3) Multiply this out:\n   x\u00b2 - 2x - \u221a2x + 2x - 2 + \u221a2 - \u221a2x + 2 - \u221a2 = 0\n\n4) Simplify:\n   x\u00b2 - 4x - 2 = 0\n\n5) Therefore, the quadratic equation is x\u00b2 - 4x - 2 = 0\n\nLet's verify the roots:\n\u2022 When x = 2+\u221a2, x\u00b2 - 4x - 2 = (2+\u221a2)\u00b2 - 4(2+\u221a2) - 2 = 0\n\u2022 When x = 2-\u221a2, x\u00b2 - 4x - 2 = (2-\u221a2)\u00b2 - 4(2-\u221a2) - 2 = 0\n\nThe equation is x\u00b2 - 4x - 2 = 0.",
